Homer MQTT-protocol

Device meta attributes for building app interfaces dynamically are available at. These can be set from the webinterface and are not managed by the device itself.
/devices/$uniquedeviceid/meta/name
														 /room

Device controlls are a available at
/devices/$uniquedeviceid/controls/power = control-value
	
For each controll, the type has to be published at 
/devices/$uniquedeviceid/controls/power/type = {"switch", "range"}


Sensors publish to 
/sensors/sensorname

Addionally, each sensor has to publish the type for each sensor to 
/sensors/sensorname/type

Currently possible values for type are: "temperature", "brightness", "count"